<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOVIES TO TAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gone with the Wind (TNT Sunday at 4 p.m.): The greatest popular movie of them 
all. (4:45) 
</P>
<P>
The Day of the Jackal (Channel 11 Monday at 1:30 a.m.): An epic-scale 1973 
suspense thriller centering on a plot to assassinate De Gaulle. Fred Zinnemann 
directed this adaptation of the Frederick Forsyth best seller. 
</P>
<P>
Que Viva Mexico! (Bravo Monday at 5 p.m.): A fascinating assemblage of Sergei 
Eisenstein's aborted 1932 poetic epic of Mexican peasantry. (1:30) 
</P>
<P>
The Ladies' Man (Channel 11 Saturday at 4 p.m.): One of Jerry Lewis' funniest, 
in which he stars as a handyman at a girls' school. Noted for its imaginative 
use of its huge single set. (2:00) 
</P>
</TEXT>
